ş ABOUT THE INTRO şÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ
  ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

    This is the  quick reference  for my first 4KB Intro which was coded for
  the Assembly'94 4KB Intro Competition.
    It is very likely that we (Dust) will release another version which will
  have Adlib Sound,  full XMS/HIMEM support and error-messages.  That wasn't
  possible in this version because of the 4KB limit.  The other intro is not
  going to be much longer than 5KB, though.
    There may also the  SOURCE-CODE coming along with that version depending
  on how many people are interested in it.

    The question what happens during the long time until the intro starts is
  easy to answer: the fractal is calculated (rotating & zooming is enough
  real-time calculations) and all tables for execution are set up.



ş HOW TO GET IT GOING şÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ
  ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

  In order to get it going, you'll need the following:

  ù preferably a 486, but it does also run on a normal 386
  ù a standard VGA
  ù about 3MB of XMS and 512KB of Base Memory (a PC with 4MB)
  ù A clean configuration. You can also have one that does only use 
    HIMEM.SYS, but you cannot use more than 192KB of XMS -> no smartdrive
  ù about 4KB of diskspace



ş TROUBLESHOOTING şÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ
  ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

    If it doesn't run (i.e. you start it and are back to DOS immediately) 
  you have (or don't have) one or more of the following:

  ù a 386 or higher processor
  ù not enough XMS memory (your PC needs 4MB altogether)
  ù not enough Base Memory (you'll need more than 512KB)
  ù the wrong configuration: remember to have a clean boot (press F5 while
    booting if you have MS-DOS 6.0 or higher), or a HIMEM-configuration. If
    you use an Expanded Memory Manager such as EMM386 or QEMM it won't run!
  ù enough time to wait for the start-up message to disappear

    If  it  hangs  during  execution  or  afterwards,  you  have  the  wrong
  configuration.



